    <cas:Sofa xmi:id="1" sofaNum="1" sofaID="_InitialView" mimeType="text" sofaString="Burkina Faso is a country with limited natural resources and highly vulnerable to climate change. Over the last 20 years, the state has been dependent on and affected by severe rain decrease due to the decline in water resources and soil degradation. The Notre Dame's Global Adaptation Index (ND-GAIN) measured Burkina Faso's levels of vulnerability to climate change as well as the readiness of countries to respond to this process; Burkina Faso is the 25th-most-vulnerable country of those assessed. That said, Burkina Faso was one of the first African countries to commit in signing the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change in 1993 and the Kyoto Protocol in 2005. Burkina Faso published its National Adaptation Plan (PNA) in September 2015, which focused on the most vulnerable sector, agriculture, water resources, livestock and forests/biodiversity. Since then, Burkina Faso has been able to sustainably strengthen agriculture's competitiveness in sectors other than cotton by increasing the income derived from agricultural exports and set up reforestation programs."/>
    <cas:View sofa="1" members="8 19 24 29 34 39 44 49 62 75 88 101 114 127 140 153 166 179 192 205 218 231 244 257 270 283 296 309 322 335 348 361 374 387 400 413 426 439 452 465 478 491 504 517 530 543 556 569 582 595 608 621 634 647 660 673 686 699 712 725 738 751 764 777 790 803 816 829 842 855 868 881 894 907 920 933 946 959 972 985 998 1011 1024 1037 1050 1063 1076 1089 1102 1115 1128 1141 1154 1167 1180 1193 1206 1219 1232 1245 1258 1271 1284 1297 1310 1323 1336 1349 1362 1375 1388 1401 1414 1427 1440 1453 1466 1479 1492 1505 1518 1531 1544 1557 1570 1583 1596 1609 1622 1635 1648 1661 1674 1687 1700 1713 1726 1739 1752 1765 1778 1791 1804 1817 1830 1843 1856 1869 1882 1895 1908 1921 1934 1947 1960 1973 1986 1999 2012 2025 2038 2051 2064 2077 2090 2103 2116 2129 2142 2155 2168 2181 2194 2207 2220 2233 2246 2259 2272 2285 2298 2311 2324 2337 2350 2363 2376 2389 2402 2415 2428 2458 2441 2446 2470 2482 2487 2499 2511 2516 2521 2463 2451 2475 2492 2504 2526 2533 2547 2540 2550 2543 2554 2567"/>
